Package com.example.flexiMed.model

Class UserEntity

java.lang.Object
com.example.flexiMed.model.UserEntity
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, org.springframework.security.core.userdetails.UserDetails
@Entity public class UserEntity extends Object implements org.springframework.security.core.userdetails.UserDetails
Entity representing a user in the system. This entity holds user information such as name, email, password, phone number, role, and profile image URL. It also implements UserDetails for Spring Security authentication purposes.

      Default constructor to initialize createdAt and version.

    • UserEntity

      public UserEntity(String name, String email, String password)
      Constructor to create a new UserEntity with name, email, and password. The userId is generated as a UUID, and createdAt and version are set automatically.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the user.
      email - The email of the user.
      password - The password of the user.

    • UserEntity

      public UserEntity(UUID userId, String name, String email, String password, String phoneNumber, Role role, String profileImageUrl)
      Constructor to create a fully initialized UserEntity with all fields.
      Parameters:
      userId - The unique ID of the user.
      name - The name of the user.
      email - The email of the user.
      password - The password of the user.
      phoneNumber - The phone number of the user.
      role - The role of the user.
      profileImageUrl - The URL of the user's profile image.
